Description: Smart AP+STA WiFi hotspot manager for Linux
 apsta lets you broadcast a WiFi hotspot while staying connected to your
 existing WiFi network simultaneously, without dropping your connection.
 .
 It detects your hardware capabilities and automatically chooses the best
 strategy: nmcli virtual interface (true concurrent AP+STA), hostapd on a
 virtual interface (Intel AX200 / iwlwifi split-block cards), or forced
 single-interface mode.
 .
 Includes:
  - apsta        — CLI hotspot manager
  - apsta-gtk    — GTK4/Libadwaita GUI (GNOME, KDE, Xfce, any GTK4 desktop)
  - cosmic-applet-apsta — COSMIC DE panel applet (Pop!_OS / COSMIC session)
